otelcol-lang
============

VS Code extension and Language Server for OpenTelemetry Collector configs.
Licensed under Apache-2.0.

This NOTICE documents the third-party software used by the extension and
language server, and the relationship to the upstream collector
distributions.


Schemas
-------

The JSON Schemas the LSP consumes for validation, hover and completion
are produced by a separate project:

  https://github.com/otelery/otelcol-schemas   (Apache-2.0)

They are bundled into the published .vsix at build time (see
`scripts/sync-schemas.mjs`). The `otelcol-schemas` repo's NOTICE
documents the upstream sources (opentelemetry-collector-contrib, the
collector core modules, vendor distributions) and the components for
which no resolvable schema exists.

A future release of this extension will gain the ability to fetch
schemas from a pinned release tag of `otelcol-schemas` at runtime; the
`otelcol.schemaSource` setting is reserved for that purpose.


Third-party runtime dependencies
--------------------------------

The extension and language server ship with the following npm packages:

  vscode-languageclient            (MIT)
  vscode-languageserver            (MIT)
  vscode-languageserver-textdocument (MIT)
  vscode-uri                       (MIT)
  yaml                             (ISC)


OTTL grammar
------------

`syntaxes/ottl.tmLanguage.json` is vendored from the `ottl-lang` project
(Apache-2.0) and injected into the `source.yaml.otelcol` scope.


Component metadata
------------------

Hover content for receivers, processors, exporters, connectors and
extensions (display name, signals, stability, codeowners, feature
gates, descriptions) is derived from each component's `metadata.yaml`
in opentelemetry-collector-contrib (Apache-2.0).
